    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "·Thedeploymentandtrainingof neuralnetworks onedge computingdevicesposemanychallenges. ·Thelowmemory nature of edgedevices is often one of thebiggest limitingfactorsencounteredinthedeploymentof largeneural networkmodels. ·Tensorrematerializationor recomputeisawaytoaddress high memoryrequirementsforneuralnetworktrainingandinference. ·In this paperwe consider the problem of execution time minimizationof computegraphssubjecttoamemorybudget. ·Inparticular,we developa newconstraint programming formulationcalledMoccasinwith onlyO(n) integervariables, where $n$ isthenumberof nodes inthe compute graph(asopposed topriorwork formulationswith $O ( n ^ { 2 } )$ variables). ",
